Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice one-quarter of the @red onion{1}; dice remaining onion. Quarter @lime{1}. Halve @green bell pepper{2} lengthwise; remove stems and seeds. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, juice from half the lime (whole lime for 4 servings), @sugar{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Microwave until onion is bright pink, ~{30%seconds}. Set aside.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups @water{1 1/4%cups} (2 ¼ cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 5.

While rice cooks, place green peppers on a #baking sheet{} and drizzle each half with @cooking oil{}; rub all over to coat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then arrange cut sides down.

Roast on top rack until browned and softened, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large, preferably ovenproof, #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add diced onion and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @ground turkey{2} (replace with tofu for vegetarian), garlic, and @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}; season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until turkey is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @tomato paste{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, and 1⁄3 cup water (1⁄2 cup for 4 servings). Reduce heat to medium low and simmer until mixture is slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> You can substitute ground turkey with tofu for a vegetarian version.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Add to pan with turkey mixture and stir until thoroughly combined; season with salt and pepper.

Once green peppers are done roasting, remove sheet from oven. Carefully flip and stuff halves with up to half the filling (save the rest for serving). Nestle each stuffed pepper in pan with remaining filling.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer stuffed peppers and filling to a #baking dish{} now.

Evenly sprinkle with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Transfer pan to top rack and roast until cheese melts, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Divide remaining filling between plates. Top with stuffed peppers and as much pickled onion (draining first) as you like.

Dollop with @smoky red pepper crema{2%tablespoon} and serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.